body.description: These LED Light Bulbs Kit is a quick and easy way to dress up your vehicle and provide a brighter visibility for AC Climate Heater Control in your cab. Please check compatibility table before ordering. Package Includes: 5 x LED Light Bulbs Compatible Vehicle: 2002-2008 Dodge Ram 1500 2003-2008 Dodge Ram 2500 2003-2008 Dodge Ram 3500 2001-2011 Dodge Dakota Note: Please confirm your AC Climate Heater Control is the same as our pictures before ordering Specifics and Features: Working Voltage: 12V Light Source: LED LED Color: White Light Count: 3 SMDs It has polarity sensitive. Make sure LED bulbs have the correct polarity before putting the climate control back, If LED doesn't light up, take the bulb out and spin it 180°. Note: If one of the lights is not locked in completely (out of the 3), none of the lights will turn on. Warranty and Customer Service: 1. 1 Year manufacturer warranty since order purchase date. 2. Feel free to send us email first if there's any issue before or after purchase. All emails will be replied within 24 hours. Your case will be taken seriously regardless of warranty period.

reviews.reviewText: These were surprisingly easy to I stall. It just took a Philips screwdriver, a pair of needle nose pliers, and about 30 minutes of my time. They are definitely brighter than factory, but that beats paying $175 for a whole new control unit at the dealership (they won’t sell you JUST) the bulbs - they only sell the whole center console HVAC control unit)

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on March 3, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Nice color and bright. The only problem I have is that dimmability of the lights is minimal. If you dim down to a point they shut off. You then shut off lights turn dimmer up then turn lights back on they work then. If you like bright these are for you.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 18, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Bright, Dimmable, Easy to install.
reviews.reviewText: Installed the blue bulbs in: 2006 Ram 1500, A/C Heater control panel. Very bright and a great improvement. No idea about longevity but will update reviews if there is an issue. Purchase package is for 5 bulbs, panel requires 3, so 2 are now spares. $8.00 well spent.Found installation tips in reviews for similar bulbs. Removed radio cowl and the AC/Heater control panel from dash. Then removed the panel's rear plastic cover (2 screws and 6 tabs). Removed existing bulbs with small needle nose pliers. by pressing down and rotated slightly counter clockwise. Lubed contacts on printed circuit board with DeOxit CP (my go to lube for electrical contacts). Then lubed the new bulb's mounting tabs with a minute quantity of SuperLube. Installed with the pliers by pressing the bulb down on the circuit board, and turning the bulbs gently clock wise. Remounted rear cover and tested. One inoperable bulb, so removed it, turned 180 degrees and re installed it. Everything was then 100%
